&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>shelly discover http</title><link>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/discover/http/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/discover/http/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="shelly-discover-http"&gt;shelly discover http&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discover devices via HTTP subnet scanning&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="synopsis"&gt;Synopsis&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discover Shelly devices by probing HTTP endpoints on a subnet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If no subnet is provided, attempts to detect the local network.
This method is slower than mDNS or CoIoT but works when multicast
is blocked or devices are on different VLANs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The scan probes each IP address in the subnet range for Shelly device
HTTP endpoints. Progress is shown in real-time. Discovered devices
can be automatically registered with &amp;ndash;register.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>shelly discover mdns</title><link>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/discover/mdns/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/discover/mdns/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="shelly-discover-mdns"&gt;shelly discover mdns&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discover devices using mDNS/Zeroconf&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="synopsis"&gt;Synopsis&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discover Shelly devices using mDNS/Zeroconf.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;mDNS (Multicast DNS) is the fastest discovery method. Devices broadcast
their presence on the local network using the _shelly._tcp.local service.
This works best for Gen2+ devices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note: mDNS requires multicast support on your network. If devices aren&amp;rsquo;t
found, try &amp;lsquo;shelly discover scan&amp;rsquo; which probes addresses directly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Output is formatted as a table showing: ID, Address, Model, Generation,
Protocol, and Auth status.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>